</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) NEW YORK -- Sept. 5, 1999 -- SHAKESPEARE-DISCO, 9-5 --
Anna Wilson in ``The Donkey Show: A Midsummer Night's Disco,''
produced with the project 400 Theater Group, which opened on Aug.
18 for a six-week run at a real club, El Flamingo in New York.
Project 400 seeks to be part of the long tradition of twisting the
confines of theater, so it is through the music, rather than any
traditional form of theater, that Shakespeare's comedy about the
vagaries of love is told. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) WASHINGTON -- Sept. 5, 1999 -- HERMAN-PROFILE, 9-5 --
Serving in Washington in the 1990s has sorely taxed the faith of
Alexis Herman, the labor secretary and one of the few remaining
survivors of every blessed day of the Clinton administration. Her
devotion has been shaken in recent years, but never to the point of
apostasy. ``It does cause me to go back and remember the early days
and the path I took to get here,'' she says. ``I try not to be
distracted by the cynicism and the negative climate in politics
today.'' (Justin Lane/New York Times Photo)
</P>
