<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-TCU-TOMLINSON-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TCU'S TOMLINSON BLISTERS ARIZONA FOR 170 YARDS IN LOSS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DARRIN SCHEID 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ TCU running back LaDainian Tomlinson needed
five games last season before reaching the 100-yard mark in a
single game, and he managed it only twice in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday night, in front of a national television audience and
against a nationally ranked opponent, Tomlinson nearly had it by
the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Despite his 91 yards in the first two quarters and TCU's early
lead, the Frogs could not hold on in a 35-31 loss to Arizona at
Amon Carter Stadium. Tomlinson, who looked like a player headed for
the TCU record books early in the game, finished with 170 yards on
28 carries for an average of 6.1 yards per rush.
</P>
<P>
   The Wildcats slowed Tomlinson to one yard on a single carry in
the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   His day wasn't near the best all-time at TCU, but it was close
to the best in Tomlinson's resume.
</P>
<P>
   A 5-foot-11, 217-pound junior from Waco, Tomlinson's best game
was in 1997 when he rushed for 180 yards against Tulsa. Sunday
night's was second-best, ahead of two games of 165 yards.
</P>
<P>
   The Wildcats had trouble early with Tomlinson's speed to the
corners, and he teamed with quarterback Patrick Batteaux on option
pitches to make Arizona pay. Tomlinson had runs of 10, 11, 15, 29,
19 and 11 yards in the first half and a rush of 29 in the third
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   In the first quarter, on a second-and-5 from the Arizona 29-yard
line, TCU pitched to Tomlinson to the left for an 11-yard gain and
a first down. On the next play, Tomlinson ran 15 yards for the
touchdown and a 9-0 TCU lead with 3:05 left in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   On first-and-20 from the Arizona 41 in the second quarter, the
Frogs elected to go with Tomlinson on four consecutive downs.
</P>
<P>
   A run for nine yards and oneyard set up a third-and-10 at the
Arizona 31. Tomlinson took an option pitch left and ran 19 yards
for the first down at the Arizona 12. After a four-yard Tomlinson
gain, TCU scored on a touchdown pass.
</P>
<P>
   In the third quarter, Tomlinson picked up seven yards and a
first down at the 25 with 4:47 left to put the Horned Frogs in
field-goal range. When the drive stalled, Chris Kaylakie kicked a
43-yard field goal to make it 28-28.
</P>
<P>
   By the end of the third, Tomlinson had 27 carries for 169 yards.
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter, the Wildcats stacked the line of
scrimmage and took TCU's running game away. The Frogs went to the
air, and they took a 31-28 lead with 13:18 left in the game.
Arizona answered with a late touchdown, and TCU's final two drives
came up empty. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-06-99 0055EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
