<P>
   GROSSMAGS-MEDIA (London) _ Too much sex may be a bad thing. At
least that is what British publishers of the so-called `laddie
magazine' market seem to be confronting as recent circulation
figures for magazines like FHM and Loaded, the originators of the
men-behaving-badly genre, dropped almost across the board. It seems
that beer and babes are in decline. Whether this presages things to
come on the western side of the Atlantic remains to be seen. By
Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
<P>
   E-COMMERCE-REVIEWS (Undated) _ E-commerce companies fill their
sites with reviews of products they sell, generally taken from
marketers or magazines, but they know that consumers frequently
give much more credence to the opinions of ``real people'' _
friends or peers who buy similar products. The problem for Internet
retailers is how to harness the opinions of those real people
without letting the negative comments chase prospective buyers
away. By Bob Tedeschi.
