<P>
   BBO-GAY-EXPLAYER _ All-America Billy Bean burst into his 20s
consumed by two struggles: to play center field in the major
leagues and to deny his homosexuality. Eventually he would have to
choose between his personal and professional lives. ``For nine
years,'' Bean said recently, ``I felt as though I had one foot in
the major leagues and one on a banana peel.'' The combination of
those two struggles offers a rare look into the fiercely
competitive and hyper-masculinized arena of major-team sports. By
Robert Lipsyte.
