the pop charts. Since teen-age artists are often one-hit wonders,
RCA Records, which gave her a seven-album contract in June 1998,
worked especially hard to create a packaging, producing and
promotion campaign for her. A look at how it was done. By Luisita
Lopez Torregrosa.
</P>
<P>
   LABORDAY-FILMS (Hollywood) _ The summer movie season typically
ends with something approaching a sigh, a little breather between
the summertime crowd pleasers and the somewhat more adult-oriented
autumn fare. What does Hollywood have against Labor Day? Labor Day
seems to be the orphan of American holidays, the ugly cousin that
no one wants to play with. By Rick Lyman.
</P>
<P>
   SHAKESPEARE-DISCO (New York) _ Puck is gliding on roller skates
through a rather misty haze that fills the dance floor, making
mischief, as Puck does, with the passions of Tytania, Sander and
Dimitri. This isn't fairyland, but rather theater, and it's done to
the pounding beat of such '70s dance hits as ``Disco Inferno.''
It's ``The Donkey Show,'' an hourlong adaptation of ``A Midsummer
Night's Dream.'' By Eric V. Copage.
