<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Plenty of top-quality, discontinued software available for free
on Web
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ There's a wonderful trend under way on the Internet
that you might want to check out. Developers are posting
discontinued commercial Mac software. It's free for the
downloading.
</P>
<P>
   This isn't shareware. It's stuff like WordPerfect, at one time
the leading contender to Word.
</P>
<P>
   The downside is that these programs are no longer supported, so
you can't expect any technical help. Nor will there be any
upgrades. You'll have to live with the programs' bugs and glitches.
</P>
<P>
   That said, much of what's available is a great deal. Take
WordPerfect, which Corel has decided to no longer develop for the
Mac. That's a shame, because this was a very good word processor.
</P>
<P>
   Now you can have this program for free. It offers 90 percent of
the features you'll find in Word.
</P>
<P>
   WordPerfect has such automated features as sentence
capitalization and correction of common misspellings. It also has
strong layout and design features. You'll find WordPerfect at
www.corel.com/products/macintosh/wpmac35/packfreedownload.htm.
</P>
<P>
   Another free word processor available online is version 4.1.6 of
Nisus Writer.
</P>
<P>
   Nisus Writer is a bit more obscure than WordPerfect, but it's
still an excellent program. Nisus Writer includes features still
incorporated in any word processor, Mac or PC. You'll find this
program at www.nisus.com/news/pr/980925.asp.
</P>
<P>
   One thing Nisus Writer doesn't have is an outliner. Now you can
find a great one for free. It's called More and, although it was
discontinued several years ago, many observers still consider the
program the best of its kind.
</P>
<P>
   More was developed by famed programmer Dave Winer, who has
regained the rights and posted the program online. You'll find More
3.1 at www.outliners
</P>
<P>
   .com/more31.html.
</P>
<P>
   More, Nisus Writer and WordPerfect are just a few examples of
what you can now find online. There are plenty of other programs
out there.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
