   SCI-DNA-VACCINE (Undated) _ Scientists at Stanford University
have found that a simple solution of DNA and water applied to the
skin of mice can induce an immune response comparable to one from
traditional intramuscular injection. The DNA vaccine was apparently
taken up through the hair follicles of the mice; nude mice (mice
without hair) did not show the same reaction. By Anne Eisenberg.
