<P>
   &UR; FRAUD  &LR; _ As e-commerce sales continue to skyrocket, more and
more consumers are falling prey to dubious business practices and
outright fraud. The number of online fraud complaints leaped from
1,280 in 1997 to 7,752 last year, according to the Internet Fraud
Watch, a consumer watchdog group in Washington. A number of
consumer groups, such as the Internet Fraud Watch and Better
Business Bureau Online, are popping up to educate the public about
the perils of conducting business in cyberspace. With:
