<DOCNO> NYT19990906.0158 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-06 17:37 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2323 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l BC-LEAH- &LR;      09-06 0727
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; AND WHO IS KISSIEST OF THEM ALL? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Capital Style magazine has named its ``Top 10 Toadies,'' the
biggest posterior-kissers in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Among the winners is presidential friend, corporate board member
and ``paragon of sucking-upward mobility''  &UR; Vernon Jordan &LR; , cited
for doing ``anything to keep the directors' fees pouring in.'' Then
there's  &UR; Larry King &LR; , whose USA Today column is a ``weekly
cavalcade of wet smooches to friends. ... It's no wonder
politicians flock to appear on `Larry King Live,' where they know
they'll face nothing but softballs.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Geraldo Rivera  &LR; is scored for his lack of credibility; and
despite ``two decades of doormat status,''  &UR; Hillary Rodham Clinton &LR; 
is described as ``seeking votes in New York by suddenly praising
retiring Sen.  &UR; Daniel Patrick Moynihan &LR; , after systematically
ignoring his expertise in health care and other areas.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Tina Brown &LR;  gets mention for ``elevating the celebrity puff
piece to an art form'' and for running a Talk magazine story on
Hillary Clinton that ``read as if it had been written by Hillary
herself.''
</P>
<P>
   The top suck-up was former presidential adviser  &UR; George &LR; 
 &UR; Stephanopoulos &LR; , for ``biting the ass he once kissed.'' The
magazine quotes Stephanopoulos' describing himself as the most
loyal staffer the Clintons ever had. ``Nobody's fought harder for
them,'' said the prize-winner, who subsequently wrote a book
excoriating his former bosses.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; - Elton John  &LR; and  &UR; Geri Halliwell &LR;  were so irritated that the
British premiere of ``Eyes Wide Shut'' started late _ stars
 &UR; Nicole Kidman  &LR; and  &UR; Tom Cruise &LR;  were greeting people in all seven
multiplex theaters where it was playing _ that they walked out
before the film began, said UK People. The movie began 75 minutes
late.
</P>
<P>
   - Budget Suites of America is staging a test run of
fingerprinting all guests when they check in. ``Personally, I'd
find it less than friendly,'' hospitality consultant  &UR; Rick &LR; 
 &UR; Stanfield &LR;  told the New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; EMERGENCY HOSE PREPARATIONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A flight attendant suggested to passengers aboard that
Sacramento-bound plane that lost a wheel on takeoff last week (and
was diverted to Ontario) that they might want to remove their
pantyhose, said a Sacramento Bee story forwarded by  &UR; Steve &LR; 
 &UR; Baker &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Although no reason was given at the time, one of the passengers
told the newspaper that the announcement implied that pantyhose are
``very flammable.'' But Southwest Airlines spokeswoman
 &UR; Melanie Jones &LR;  said later that it might be a ``matter of comfort.
In case of evacuation by inflatable slides, it's more comfortable
if you don't wear pantyhose because it can cause friction on your
legs.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; KITCHEN MAGIC &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Curmudgeon's Home Companion newsletter proclaims itself
``astounded'' by the advent of Crabtree &AMP; Evelyn's ``cooking
sprays,'' which make the kitchen smell as though something is
cooking. ``Evidently,'' writes the Curmudgeon, ``there are quite a
few people willing to pay $4.99 to conceal the fact that they
haven't cooked a meal in months.''
</P>
<P>
   The aroma choices include Patisserie, Cranberry Compote, Salad
Greens and Orange Ginger.
</P>
<P>
   P.S. Don't confuse the flyswatter with the fondue fork:  &UR; Nancy &LR; 
 &UR; Scott  &LR; was taken with the Andronico's ad for Aged French Gruyere
Comte, which specifies that the cheese is ``excellent with bread, a
good bottle of red wine and a front porch.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PASTIMES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - If you're a  &UR; George W.  &LR; kind of person, you might look at
 &LR; bushwear.com cq &LR; , where two out of six items are related to golf.
</P>
<P>
   - Lord  &UR; Frederick Windsor &LR; , son of  &UR; Prince &LR;  and  &UR; Princess
Michael &LR;  of Kent, 20 years old and 28th in line for the throne of
England, has admitted snorting cocaine at a party three months ago.
``It is very difficult to avoid getting into this sort of thing,
but I don't blame anyone else for the incident,'' he told the Times
of London.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I love my breasts because they were never there before. And
now, I wake up in the morning and they look at me in the mirror and
say, `hello, Leelee!' I put them away in a shirt, but I always
leave a little bit showing.''
</P>
<P>
   - Actress  &UR; Leelee Sobieski &LR; , 17, in Seventeen magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
