   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TV-TEENS _ Here they come, barreling down their high school
hallway, three high school girls, each better-looking and more
stuck-up than the next, cutting through the losers clogging the
hallway, snapping out: ``Move. Move. Move.'' That one scene, in
Fox's upcoming be-cruel-to-your-school series ``Manchester Prep,''
nicely sums up the coming onslaught of new fall TV shows: Get out
of the way, geezers. The kids are here. Never before has there been
such a one-time flood of new shows set in high schools, or about
teenagers and their families, as in the coming fall television
season. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
