MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - There are moments in baseball that
aren't like anything else in sport because, in those moments,
everything changes and the game isn't about sport anymore but about
life. That's what happened Sunday afternoon in Atlanta when
Diamondback's catcher Kelly Stinnett, batting with two outs in the
top of the ninth inning and his team down by a run, struck out. By
EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
