   SCI-TSIEN-MOUSE (Undated) _ A Scientist-at-Work profile: The
world has been frenetically beating on the door of Joe Z. Tsien,
the biologist who announced last week he had created a smarter
strain of mouse. Within this enveloping chaos, Tsien has spun
around himself a small bubble of protective serenity. He calmly
describes the remarkable journey that led him from Wu Shi, a small
town near Shanghai, to the position of having made a significant,
maybe decisive, contribution to understanding the nature of memory.
By Nicholas Wade. (2000 words)
