here. The design is a titanium and glass bubble-shaped structure
that sits in the middle of a vast lake and is entered via an
underwater tunnel. It will quickly redefine the landscape in the
sedate, conservative political heart of Beijing, adding the first
touch of modern Western architecture. By Elisabeth Rosenthal.
