<HEADER>
A2486 &Cx1f; taf-z
u f BC-FINANCIER-ARRESTED-NY     09-06 0314
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FINANCIER-ARRESTED-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXTRADITION HEARING ON ALLEGED EMBEZZLER IS AWAITED 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By EDMUND L. ANDREWS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HAMBURG, Germany _ Martin Frankel, the money manager sought on
charges that he embezzled hundreds of millions of dollars, spent
another day in prison as German prosecutors waited for American
law-enforcement officials to formally ask for his extradition to
the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Rudiger Bagger, the Hamburg prosecutor, said that police had
charged Frankel with violating German laws by carrying a false
passport. The charge is minor compared with those leveled against
Frankel in the United States, but it makes it easier to hold him in
prison while German officials wait for more detailed evidence from
their U.S. counterparts.
</P>
<P>
   Bagger said that a hearing on Frankel's extradition may be held
as early as Thursday, but that it would probably take several weeks
before he is actually sent back to the United States.
</P>
<P>
   German police officials, acting on a request from the FBI,
arrested Frankel at a Hamburg hotel on Saturday night. Frankel and
a companion, Cynthia Allison, stayed at the elegant Hotel Prem for
about eight weeks under assumed names.
</P>
<P>
   Frankel, who is 44, had been a fugitive since early May, when he
became engulfed in accusations of having systematically embezzled
at least $200 million from insurance companies that had invested
money with him.
</P>
<P>
   Though German prosecutors do not expect any problems in
extraditing Frankel, Bagger said that the FBI's arrest warrant
provided only the most general allegations with few specific facts
to back them up.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. prosecutors will have to send extensive information and
supporting documents here concerning the crimes that Frankel is
charged with committing, but that information is not expected to
arrive until later this week at the earliest.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-06-99 2017EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
