<P>
   ISRAEL-RIGHTS (Jerusalem) _ In a watershed ruling, the Israeli
Supreme Court today unexpectedly outlawed the security service's
practice of using physically coercive interrogation methods, which
critics have long denounced as torture. By Deborah Sontag. (The
story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,500 words.
</P>
