   GUNS-POLICE-CHIEFS (Boston) _ Chiefs of police across the nation
are turning to gun control as a key factor in crime control
programs and are now pushing for tougher gun laws. A group of
chiefs will meet in Washington this week to lobby for gun laws. By
Fox Butterfield. (Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``a'' news
file.) 1,100 words.
</P>
<P>
   NY-ANCIENT-SKULL (New York) _ An intriguing fossil skull,
presumably from a Homo erectus and possibly a revealing piece of
evidence for understanding human evolution, has been found, not on
a parched hill in Africa or along a river in Java, but at a little
shop in Manhattan. Paleoanthropologists have concluded that it is a
genuine specimen from Indonesia and could be critical in
determining the place of the Homo erectus species in East Asia on
the human family tree. By John Noble Wilford. (Scheduled to move by
9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
