took down signs to bring to end the summer season on the beach in
Heckscher State Park. Traditionally seen as the end of summer, many
lifeguards at beaches and pools around the nation marked their last
day of work on Monday. (James Estrin/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) JERUSALEM -- Sept. 6, 1999 -- ISRAEL-RIGHTS, 09-06 -- A
torture technique alleged to be used on Palestinian prisoners by
Shin Bet, Israel's internal security service, is demonstrated to
reporters by the Israeli human rights group Betzelem in May, 1998.
During interrogation a prisoner is covered with a sac while his
arms and legs are chained to a chair for hours. Israel's Supreme
