   (NYT22) SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Sept. 6, 1999 -- COLLEGE-GUIDANCE,
09-06 -- Students at Silver Creek High School listen to Jeff
Livingston, counseling director for Achieva, about college
application requirements last month. In a trend that educators say
is sure to spread, a growing number of public schools, most of them
in California, as well as others in Michigan, Illinois and
Missouri, are engaging firms like Achieva and the better-known
Princeton Review to relieve guidance counselors of major aspects of
college and career advising. (Thor Swift/New York Times Photo)
